name: san-francisco-bay-area-rural-investment-areas-september-2012
notes: Rural Investment Areas (RIAs) represent areas where local jurisdictions are planning for new growth. As part of the Sustainable Communities Strategy, RIAs do not have the same status as Priority Development Areas (PDAs). RIAs lost Priority Development Area status following action taken by the Association of Bay Area Governments' Executive Board, in July 2012, to remove employment and rural place types from the list of PDAs. Rural Investment Areas will still be used to model and plan for future growth as part of the Sustainable Communities Strategy, including the development of Plan Bay Area, but they will no longer be eligible for regional funds designated to facilitate development within Priority Development Areas.
